description.narrative:
1.Existence of cooperation mechanism for stakeholders consultation in implementation issues;
2.Level of knowledge by consultative body members and relevant state officials on international principles and standards on cooperation in rule of Law matters;
3. Existence of the training program and methodology on capacity development of key Rule of Law institutions as part of judicial reform implementation process;
4. Availability of methodology on financial assessments of Judicial Laws.                                        
5. Existence of  national capacity for donor coordination;
6. Number  and capacity of CSOs  engaged in the Judicial  reform process;
7. Existence of civil society mechanism for engagement in Rule of Law implementation reform process.

comment.narrative:
1. Lack of formal mechanism of cooperation between RoL related stakeholders;
2. Lack of knowledge on international principles and standards on cooperation in rule of Law matters;
3.  Lack of synchronized training program and methodology on capacity building of key RoL institutions as part of the judicial reform implementation;
4. Lack of methodology in performing financial assessments upon submission of the Laws to the Parliament and after adoption;
5. Lack of national capacity for interface with international donors on financial planning for Rule of Law reforms;
6. Only seven CSOs engaged in the Rule of Law reforms and their capacity is limited to provide quality expert advice;
7. Lack of mechanism for civil society engagement in Rule of Law implementation reform process.

1.Support is provided to implementation of 6 UPR recommendations relevant to the project:

5.21 Strengthen national procedures for the protection of the rights of vulnerable groups, including women, children, the disabled and the elderly; 
5.34 Continue the implementation of measures aimed to empower women and their contribution into society;
5.58. Combat violence against women;
5.61 Adopt a national action plan to combat violence against women and a law on domestic violence;
5.130 Implement the series of measures to ensure the rights of and improve the quality of life of persons with disabilities for 2014-2017;
7.1 Ratify Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities.

2.New Law of Free Legal Aid is adopted by the Parliament in November 2016 and signed by the President of KR in December 2016. New FLA law includes a norm on providing citizens the right to receive free legal aid in civil cases effective as of 2018. 

3. 605 representatives of formal and informal justice institutions were trained on the rights of vulnerable groups of population, access to justice and delivery of legal aid. 
Training modules on the rights of women, children, youth and people with disabilities were developed, tested and finalized also including ethic norms of working with the target groups.

4. Five more FLA centers of the Ministry of Justice were opened and made operational in Chui and Osh provinces. Ten MoJ FLA centers provided 3 512 consultations to 2 967 people (1 854 women and 1 113 men).
NGO - LBD Consulting provided 2 809 oral, 3 390 written, 98 representations at court and 82 representations out of court to 5 863 people (4 217 women and 1 646 men).
Legal clinic under the Kyrgyz-Russia Slavonic University provided 132 consultations: 102 oral and 30 written. 
Public reception of the Ministry of Labor and Social Development was equipped in Osh province and connected to Bishkek office via video-conference. 
Public receptions of the MoLSD received 1 383 complaints and appeal

1.1 Law on Protection from Domestic Violence (PDV) was signed by the President of KR in April 2017.
Law of the Kyrgyz Republic “On amending some legislative acts on the rights and guarantees of persons with disabilities” to eliminate  some norms in legislation that infringe PwDs’ rights, including legal regime of the facsimile signature and status of sign language interpreters was signed by the President of KR in June 2017. 
Support to a dialogue between all parties on ratification of the UN CRPD is provided:
-	Conference on the results of the monitoring of the Government’s programme "Set of measures to ensure the rights and improve the quality of life of persons with disabilities in the Kyrgyz Republic, 2014-2017” implementation conducted;
-	A package of legislative acts: draft resolution of the KR Government on the draft Law “On ratification of UN CRPD”, justification to the draft regulation, the bill “On the ratification of the UN Convention on the rights of persons with disabilities” and justification to the bill developed;
-	informational campaign to promote the process of UN CRPD ratification conducted.

1.2 The Government of KR adopted a decree “On establishment of the FLA Coordination Center under the Ministry of Justice” with 22 Coordinators (decree of the Government dated 31 May 2017, № 314).

